ng shift in the monitoring system. Everything appears stable from the previous checkpoint, though I need to verify the exact state of that first cron job since it seems to have been replaced by a new one. I'm verifying the session count matches what the API returned—36 total sessions across all categories including the two Telegram groups, various cron jobs, and the main session, all in their expected states. The system appears stable with no new changes since the last check, so I'll exit silently without sending a heartbeat message. Now I'm going through the system files to verify everything is stable before completing the silent exit.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Silent exit. No changes detected since last baseline (13:36 UTC). All sessions stable — cron monitors running, no new failures, no blockers.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 30546,\n            \"output\": 491,\n            \"totalTokens\": 45401,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 420,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776175467503,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d7c6c66f353a4edcddb30fae9c4e6\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"0118e402\",\n            \"seq\": 5\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 