{"type":"message","id":"a9961b64","parentId":"5c137859","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:05:39.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full sessions list. Let me analyze the active master-orchestrator sessions (excluding this cron session):\n\n1. **This cron session**: `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` - running - Agent Status to Lead (this session itself)\n\n2. **cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7** - running - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\" (QLHV ecosystem) - startedAt: 1776172286015 → running for ~54 minutes (from 13:51 to 14:05 UTC)\n   \n3. **cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31** - running - \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" (DTLX ecosystem) - startedAt: 1776152701090 → running for ~6h 39m (started around 07:25 UTC)\n\n4. **telegram:direct:6053576134** - done - Lead direct session (received the 13:55 UTC report)\n\n5. **telegram:group:-5163901258** - still active in the Telegram group session\n\n6. **cron:b653a6c0-143b-4b53-a242-034bc5fd9fca** - still running but looks like an orphaned cron job with no activity, likely a zombie that needs cleanup\n\n7. **cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff** - another zombie session, same issue with no messages\n\nThe rest are either completed or failed subagents and child sessions that aren't relevant here. So filtering down, I've got this cron session plus three others still actively running. Looking at the execution times for these sessions. The first one ran for about 54 minutes, the second for roughly 6 hours and 39 minutes, and this current session is just starting up. Now I need to figure out how to format this for the report to send to Lead.","thinkingSignature":"c507812ebf2d612589a4c4968557f2ea72dba4ce99711e3d20fe7bcbf870c448"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll compile the report and send it to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ks7ppo3jkea7_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-